                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.5112 France/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Herrick</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-10T14:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1927—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>172. Tour telegram No. 231, June 2, 9 p.m. According to <hi rend="italic">New
                        York Times</hi> today Briand has made his proposal in definite form and on
                    June 3 gave you a note explaining his idea of how the pact should be framed. It
                    was also stated that the note has been forwarded to Washington.</p>
                <p>The Department wishes to be informed whether such a note has been received. If it
                    has, please telegraph summary of contents.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
